Sentencas: Microstructure, thermal expansion and electrical conductivity of YBaCo2O5+delta cathode material was studied for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) based on yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolytes.
Titulo: YBaCo2O5+δ as a new cathode material for zirconia-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: YBaCo2O5+delta exhibits metallic conduction behavior and the conductivity of sigma = 153-35 S/cm from 100 to 800 degrees C was observed.
Titulo: YBaCo2O5+δ as a new cathode material for zirconia-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal expansion of sample shows a linear characteristics and the average thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) is about 1.45 x 10(-5)/K in the temperature range of 200-800 degrees C. YBaCo2O5+delta-Ag composite cathode was prepared and applied onto YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: YBaCo2O5+δ as a new cathode material for zirconia-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The microstructural and electrochemical characterizations of obtained electrode-electrolyte sample were examined.
Titulo: YBaCo2O5+δ as a new cathode material for zirconia-based solid oxide fuel cells
